  21class PythonText:
  22    """
  23    Class for holding text representation of Python, with possible additional annotations.
  24    str() method returns only the text for interoperability.
  25    """
  26
  27    s: str
  28    is_in_parens: bool
  29
  30    def __init__(self, s: str, *, is_in_parens: bool = False):
  31        assert isinstance(s, str)
  32        assert isinstance(is_in_parens, bool)
  33        self.s = s
  34        self.is_in_parens = is_in_parens
  35
  36    def __str__(self):
  37        return self.s
  38
  39    def __repr__(self):
  40        return self.s.__repr__()

 129class PreTerm(abc.ABC):
 130    """
 131    abstract base class, without combination ability
 132    """
 133
 134    source_string: Union[str, None]
 135
 136    def __init__(self):
 137        self.source_string = None
 138
 139    @abc.abstractmethod
 140    def is_equal(self, other):
 141        """
 142        Check if this expression code is the same as another expression.
 143        """
 144        # can't use == as that builds a larger expression
 145
 146    # tree re-write
 147
 148    @abc.abstractmethod
 149    def get_views(self):
 150        """
 151        return list of unique views, expectation list is of size zero or one
 152        """
 153
 154    @abc.abstractmethod
 155    def replace_view(self, view):
 156        """
 157        Move expression to a new view.
 158        """
 159
 160    # analysis
 161
 162    def get_column_names(self, columns_seen: Set[str]) -> None:
 163        """
 164        Add column names to columns_seen
 165        :param columns_seen: set of strings
 166        :return: None
 167        """
 168        pass
 169
 170    def get_method_names(self, methods_seen: Set[str]) -> None:
 171        """
 172        Add method names to methods_seen
 173        :param methods_seen: set of strings
 174        :return: None
 175        """
 176        pass
 177
 178    # eval
 179
 180    @abc.abstractmethod
 181    def evaluate(self, data_frame):
 182        """
 183        Evaluate expression, taking data from data_frame.
 184        """
 185
 186    # emitters
 187
 188    @abc.abstractmethod
 189    def to_python(self, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> PythonText:
 190        """
 191        Convert parsed expression into a string
 192
 193        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
 194        :return: PythonText
 195        """
 196
 197    def to_source(self, *, want_inline_parens=False, dialect="Python") -> PythonText:
 198        """
 199        Convert to source code.
 200
 201        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
 202        :param dialect: dialect to emit (not currently used)
 203        :return: PythonText
 204        """
 205        if dialect == "Python":
 206            return self.to_python(want_inline_parens=want_inline_parens)
 207        else:
 208            raise ValueError("unexpected dialect string: " + str(dialect))
 209
 210    # printing
 211
 212    def __repr__(self):
 213        return str(self.to_python(want_inline_parens=False))
 214
 215    def __str__(self):
 216        return str(self.to_python(want_inline_parens=False))

 219def _is_none_value(x):
 220    if x is None:
 221        return True
 222    if isinstance(x, Value):
 223        return x.value is None
 224    return False
 225
 226
 227def _check_expr_incompatible_types(a, b):
 228    """
 229    return None if no type problem, else return pair of types
 230    """
 231
 232    def obvious_declared_type(v):
 233        """
 234        Return type of value, if obvious (usually it is not).
 235        """
 236        if v is None:
 237            return None  # None may be a placeholder for "don't know at this point"
 238        if isinstance(v, Value):
 239            return type(v.value)
 240        if isinstance(v, ColumnReference):
 241            return None
 242        if isinstance(v, PreTerm):
 243            return None
 244        return None  # dunno
 245
 246    type_a = obvious_declared_type(a)
 247    if type_a is None:
 248        return None
 249    type_b = obvious_declared_type(b)
 250    if type_b is None:
 251        return None
 252    looks_compatible = data_algebra.util.compatible_types([type_a, type_b])
 253    if looks_compatible:
 254        return None
 255    return type_a, type_b

 258# noinspection SpellCheckingInspection
 259class Term(PreTerm, abc.ABC):
 260    """
 261    Abstract intermediate class with combination ability
 262    """
 263
 264    def __init__(self):
 265        PreTerm.__init__(self)
 266
 267    # builders
 268
 269    def __op_expr__(self, op, other, *, inline=True, method=False, check_types=True):
 270        """binary expression"""
 271        assert isinstance(op, str)
 272        if not isinstance(other, Term):
 273            other = enc_value(other)
 274        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 275        assert not _is_none_value(other)
 276        if check_types:
 277            obvious_type_problem = _check_expr_incompatible_types(self, other)
 278            if obvious_type_problem is not None:
 279                raise TypeError(
 280                    f"trying to combine incompatible values:"
 281                    + f" {self}:{obvious_type_problem[0]}"
 282                    + f" and {other}:{obvious_type_problem[0]} with {op}"
 283                )
 284        return Expression(op, (self, other), inline=inline, method=method)
 285
 286    def __rop_expr__(self, op, other, *, check_types=True):
 287        """reversed binary expression"""
 288        inline = True
 289        method = False
 290        assert isinstance(op, str)
 291        if not isinstance(other, Term):
 292            other = enc_value(other)
 293        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 294        assert not _is_none_value(other)
 295        if check_types:
 296            obvious_type_problem = _check_expr_incompatible_types(self, other)
 297            if obvious_type_problem is not None:
 298                raise TypeError(
 299                    f"trying to combine incompatible values:"
 300                    + f" {other}:{obvious_type_problem[0]}"
 301                    + f" and {self}:{obvious_type_problem[0]} with {op}"
 302                )
 303        return Expression(op, (other, self), inline=inline, method=method)
 304
 305    def __uop_expr__(self, op, *, params=None, inline=False):
 306        """unary expression"""
 307        assert isinstance(op, str)
 308        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 309        return Expression(op, (self,), params=params, inline=inline, method=not inline)
 310
 311    def __triop_expr__(self, op, x, y, inline=False, method=False):
 312        """three argument expression"""
 313        assert isinstance(op, str)
 314        if not isinstance(x, Term):
 315            x = enc_value(x)
 316        if not isinstance(y, Term):
 317            y = enc_value(y)
 318        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 319        return Expression(op, (self, x, y), inline=inline, method=method)

1033class Value(Term):
1034    """
1035    Class for holding constants.
1036    """
1037
1038    def __init__(self, value):
1039        allowed = {
1040            data_algebra.util.map_type_to_canonical(t)
1041            for t in [int, float, str, bool, type(None)]
1042        }
1043        disallowed = {data_algebra.util.map_type_to_canonical(type(value))} - allowed
1044        if len(disallowed) != 0:
1045            raise TypeError(
1046                "value type must be one of: "
1047                + str(allowed)
1048                + ", saw "
1049                + str(list(disallowed)[0])
1050            )
1051        self.value = value
1052        Term.__init__(self)
1053
1054    def is_equal(self, other):
1055        """
1056        Check if this expression code is the same as another expression.
1057        """
1058        # can't use == as that builds a larger expression
1059        if not isinstance(other, Value):
1060            return False
1061        return self.value == other.value
1062
1063    def get_views(self):
1064        """
1065        return list of unique views, expectation list is of size zero or one
1066        """
1067        views = list()
1068        return views
1069
1070    def replace_view(self, view):
1071        """
1072        Move expression to a new view.
1073        """
1074        return self
1075
1076    def evaluate(self, data_frame):
1077        """
1078        Evaluate expression, taking data from data_frame.
1079        """
1080        return self.value
1081
1082    def to_python(self, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> PythonText:
1083        """
1084        Convert parsed expression into a string
1085
1086        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
1087        :return: PythonText
1088        """
1089        return PythonText(self.value.__repr__(), is_in_parens=False)
1090
1091    # don't collect -5 as a complex expression
1092    def __neg__(self):
1093        return Value(-self.value)

1096class ListTerm(PreTerm):
1097    """
1098    Class to hold a collection.
1099    """
1100
1101    # derived from PreTerm as this is not combinable
1102    def __init__(self, value):
1103        assert isinstance(value, (list, tuple))
1104        self.value = [v for v in value]  # copy and standardize to a list
1105        PreTerm.__init__(self)
1106
1107    def is_equal(self, other):
1108        """
1109        Check if this expression code is the same as another expression.
1110        """
1111        # can't use == as that builds a larger expression
1112        if not isinstance(other, ListTerm):
1113            return False
1114        return self.value == other.value
1115
1116    def get_views(self):
1117        """
1118        return list of unique views, expectation list is of size zero or one
1119        """
1120        views = list()
1121        for ai in self.value:
1122            if isinstance(ai, PreTerm):
1123                vi = ai.get_views()
1124                for vii in vi:
1125                    if vii not in views:  # expect list to be of size zero or one
1126                        views.append(vii)
1127        return views
1128
1129    def replace_view(self, view):
1130        """
1131        Move expression to a new view.
1132        """
1133        new_list = [ai.replace_view(view) for ai in self.value]
1134        return ListTerm(new_list)
1135
1136    def evaluate(self, data_frame):
1137        """
1138        Evaluate expression, taking data from data_frame.
1139        """
1140        res = [None] * len(self.value)
1141        for i in range(len(self.value)):
1142            vi = self.value[i]
1143            if isinstance(vi, PreTerm):
1144                vi = vi.evaluate(data_frame)
1145            res[i] = vi
1146        return res
1147
1148    def to_python(self, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> PythonText:
1149        """
1150        Convert parsed expression into a string
1151
1152        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
1153        :return: PythonText
1154        """
1155
1156        def li_to_python(value):
1157            """convert a list item to Python"""
1158            try:
1159                return str(value.to_python(want_inline_parens=False))
1160            except AttributeError:
1161                return str(value)  # TODO: check if this should be repr?
1162
1163        return PythonText(
1164            "[" + ", ".join([li_to_python(ai) for ai in self.value]) + "]",
1165            is_in_parens=False,
1166        )
1167
1168    def get_column_names(self, columns_seen: Set[str]) -> None:
1169        """
1170        Add column names to columns_seen
1171        :param columns_seen: set of strings
1172        :return:
1173        """
1174        for ti in self.value:
1175            ti.get_column_names(columns_seen)

1186        PreTerm.__init__(self)

1189        """
1190        Check if this expression code is the same as another expression.
1191        """
1192        # can't use == as that builds a larger expression
1193        if not isinstance(other, DictTerm):
1194            return False
1195        return self.value == other.value
1196
1197    def get_views(self):
1198        """
1199        return list of unique views, expectation list is of size zero or one
1200        """
1201        views = list()
1202        return views

1204    def replace_view(self, view):
1205        """
1206        Move expression to a new view.
1207        """
1208        return DictTerm(self.value)
1209
1210    def evaluate(self, data_frame):
1211        """
1212        Evaluate expression, taking data from data_frame.
1213        """
1214        return self.value.copy()
1215
1216    def to_python(self, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> PythonText:
1217        """
1218        Convert parsed expression into a string
1219
1220        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
1221        :return: PythonText
1222        """
1223
1224        def li_to_python(value):
1225            """Convert an item to python"""
1226            try:
1227                return str(value.to_python(want_inline_parens=False))
1228            except AttributeError:
1229                return value.__repr__()
1230
1231        terms = [
1232            li_to_python(k) + ": " + li_to_python(v) for k, v in self.value.items()
1233        ]
1234        return PythonText("{" + ", ".join(terms) + "}", is_in_parens=False)

1237def enc_value(value):
1238    """
1239    Encode a value as a PreTerm or derived class.
1240    """
1241    if isinstance(value, PreTerm):
1242        return value
1243    if callable(value):
1244        raise ValueError("can't use a callable as an argument")
1245    if isinstance(value, list):
1246        return ListTerm(value)
1247    return Value(value)

1319# noinspection SpellCheckingInspection
1320def _can_find_method_by_name(op):
1321    assert isinstance(op, str)
1322    # from populate_specials
1323    if op in {
1324        "_count",
1325        "_row_number",
1326        "_size",
1327        "_connected_components",
1328        "_ngroup",
1329        "_uniform",
1330    }:
1331        return True
1332    # check user fns
1333    # first check chosen mappings
1334    try:
1335        # noinspection PyUnusedLocal
1336        check_val = data_algebra.default_data_model.user_fun_map[op]  # for KeyError
1337        return True
1338    except KeyError:
1339        pass
1340    # check chosen mappings
1341    try:
1342        # noinspection PyUnusedLocal
1343        check_val = data_algebra.default_data_model.impl_map[op]  # for KeyError
1344        return True
1345    except KeyError:
1346        pass
1347    # now see if argument (usually Pandas) can do this
1348    # doubt we hit in this, as most exposed methods are window methods
1349    try:
1350        method = getattr(Value(0), op)
1351        if callable(method):
1352            return True
1353    except AttributeError:
1354        pass
1355    return False

1358class Expression(Term):
1359    """
1360    Class for carrying an expression.
1361    """
1362
1363    def __init__(
1364        self, op: str, args, *, params=None, inline: bool = False, method: bool = False
1365    ):
1366        assert isinstance(op, str)
1367        if not _can_find_method_by_name(op):
1368            raise KeyError(f"can't find implementation for function/method {op}")
1369        if inline:
1370            if method:
1371                raise ValueError("can't set both inline and method")
1372        self.op = op
1373        self.args = [enc_value(ai) for ai in args]
1374        self.params = params
1375        self.inline = inline
1376        self.method = method
1377        Term.__init__(self)
1378
1379    def is_equal(self, other):
1380        """
1381        Check if this expression code is the same as another expression.
1382        """
1383        # can't use == as that builds a larger expression
1384        if not isinstance(other, Expression):
1385            return False
1386        if self.op != other.op:
1387            return False
1388        if self.inline != other.inline:
1389            return False
1390        if self.params is None:
1391            if other.params is not None:
1392                return False
1393        else:
1394            if set(self.params.keys()) != set(other.params.keys()):
1395                return False
1396            for k in self.params.keys():
1397                if self.params[k] != other.params[k]:
1398                    return False
1399        if len(self.args) != len(other.args):
1400            return False
1401        for lft, rgt in zip(self.args, other.args):
1402            if not lft.is_equal(rgt):
1403                return False
1404        return True
1405
1406    def get_views(self):
1407        """
1408        return list of unique views, expectation list is of size zero or one
1409        """
1410        views = list()
1411        for ai in self.args:
1412            vi = ai.get_views()
1413            for vii in vi:
1414                if vii not in views:  # expect list to be of size zero or one
1415                    views.append(vii)
1416        return views
1417
1418    def replace_view(self, view):
1419        """
1420        Move expression to a new view.
1421        """
1422        new_args = [oi.replace_view(view) for oi in self.args]
1423        return Expression(
1424            op=self.op,
1425            args=new_args,
1426            params=self.params,
1427            inline=self.inline,
1428            method=self.method,
1429        )
1430
1431    def get_column_names(self, columns_seen: Set[str]) -> None:
1432        """
1433        Add column names to columns_seen
1434        :param columns_seen: set of strings
1435        :return:
1436        """
1437        for a in self.args:
1438            a.get_column_names(columns_seen)
1439
1440    def get_method_names(self, methods_seen: Set[str]) -> None:
1441        """
1442        Add names of methods used to methods_seen.
1443
1444        :param methods_seen: set to collect results
1445        :return: None
1446        """
1447        methods_seen.add(self.op)
1448
1449    def evaluate(self, data_frame):
1450        """
1451        Evaluate expression, taking data from data_frame.
1452        """
1453        args = [ai.evaluate(data_frame) for ai in self.args]
1454        # check user fns
1455        # first check chosen mappings
1456        try:
1457            method_to_call = data_algebra.default_data_model.user_fun_map[self.op]
1458            return method_to_call(*args)
1459        except KeyError:
1460            pass
1461        # check chosen mappings
1462        try:
1463            method_to_call = data_algebra.default_data_model.impl_map[self.op]
1464            return method_to_call(*args)
1465        except KeyError:
1466            pass
1467        # special zero argument functions
1468        if len(args) == 0:
1469            if self.op == "_uniform":
1470                return numpy.random.uniform(size=data_frame.shape[0])
1471            else:
1472                KeyError(f"zero-argument function {self.op} not found")
1473        # now see if argument (usually Pandas) can do this
1474        # doubt we hit in this, as most exposed methods are window methods
1475        try:
1476            method = getattr(args[0], self.op)
1477            if callable(method):
1478                return method(*args[1:])
1479        except AttributeError:
1480            pass
1481        # new see if numpy can do this
1482        try:
1483            fn = numpy.__dict__[self.op]
1484            if callable(fn):
1485                return fn(*args)
1486        except KeyError:
1487            pass
1488        raise KeyError(f"function {self.op} not found")
1489
1490    def to_python(self, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> PythonText:
1491        """
1492        Convert parsed expression into a string
1493
1494        :param want_inline_parens: bool, if True put parens around complex expressions that don't already have a grouper.
1495        :return: PythonText
1496        """
1497        n_args = len(self.args)
1498        if n_args <= 0:
1499            return PythonText(self.op + "()", is_in_parens=False)
1500        if n_args == 1:
1501            sub_0 = self.args[0].to_python(want_inline_parens=False)
1502            if self.inline:
1503                if sub_0.is_in_parens:
1504                    return PythonText(self.op + str(sub_0), is_in_parens=False)
1505                return PythonText(self.op + "(" + str(sub_0) + ")", is_in_parens=False)
1506            if self.method:
1507                if sub_0.is_in_parens or isinstance(self.args[0], ColumnReference):
1508                    return PythonText(
1509                        str(sub_0) + "." + self.op + "()", is_in_parens=False
1510                    )
1511                return PythonText(
1512                    "(" + str(sub_0) + ")." + self.op + "()", is_in_parens=False
1513                )
1514        if self.inline:
1515            subs_strs = [str(ai.to_python(want_inline_parens=True)) for ai in self.args]
1516            result = (" " + self.op + " ").join(subs_strs)
1517            if want_inline_parens:
1518                return PythonText("(" + result + ")", is_in_parens=True)
1519            return PythonText(result, is_in_parens=False)
1520        subs: List[PythonText] = [
1521            ai.to_python(want_inline_parens=False) for ai in self.args
1522        ]
1523        subs_0 = subs[0]
1524        subs_strs = [str(si) for si in subs]
1525        if self.method:
1526            if subs_0.is_in_parens or isinstance(self.args[0], ColumnReference):
1527                return PythonText(
1528                    subs_strs[0] + "." + self.op + "(" + ", ".join(subs_strs[1:]) + ")",
1529                    is_in_parens=False,
1530                )
1531            else:
1532                return PythonText(
1533                    "("
1534                    + subs_strs[0]
1535                    + ")."
1536                    + self.op
1537                    + "("
1538                    + ", ".join(subs_strs[1:])
1539                    + ")",
1540                    is_in_parens=False,
1541                )
1542        # treat as fn call
1543        return PythonText(
1544            self.op + "(" + ", ".join(subs_strs) + ")", is_in_parens=False
1545        )

 270    def __op_expr__(self, op, other, *, inline=True, method=False, check_types=True):
 271        """binary expression"""
 272        assert isinstance(op, str)
 273        if not isinstance(other, Term):
 274            other = enc_value(other)
 275        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 276        assert not _is_none_value(other)
 277        if check_types:
 278            obvious_type_problem = _check_expr_incompatible_types(self, other)
 279            if obvious_type_problem is not None:
 280                raise TypeError(
 281                    f"trying to combine incompatible values:"
 282                    + f" {self}:{obvious_type_problem[0]}"
 283                    + f" and {other}:{obvious_type_problem[0]} with {op}"
 284                )
 285        return Expression(op, (self, other), inline=inline, method=method)
 286
 287    def __rop_expr__(self, op, other, *, check_types=True):
 288        """reversed binary expression"""
 289        inline = True
 290        method = False
 291        assert isinstance(op, str)
 292        if not isinstance(other, Term):
 293            other = enc_value(other)
 294        assert not _is_none_value(self)
 295        assert not _is_none_value(other)
 296        if check_types:
 297            obvious_type_problem = _check_expr_incompatible_types(self, other)

 299                raise TypeError(

 301                    + f" {other}:{obvious_type_problem[0]}"
 302                    + f" and {self}:{obvious_type_problem[0]} with {op}"

1383        """

1385        if not isinstance(other, Expression):
1386            return False

1388            return False
1389        if self.inline != other.inline:
1390            return False

1392            if other.params is not None:
1393                return False

1395            if set(self.params.keys()) != set(other.params.keys()):
1396                return False

1399                    return False
